summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Twelve ($12.00) Dollars out of the Light Fund of the City of Seattle in settlement of the claim of J. E. Houghton and George C. Houghton for damages to personal property sustained by them on May 8, 1916, at the intersection of 63rd Street and Ravenna Boulavrd, in said city, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
